\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\widctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af10\langfe2052\ql\ltrpar{\loch
Excellent! Okay, so, a problem I realized that I'll need your help with. So, I want to implement "Minmax" questlines, unique interactions, etc etc etc and so on and so forth. At the same time, I also want to implement a top-down, turn-based, isometric version of the "Berserk"/"Sandevistan"(Framejacking)/"Overclock" functionality from Cyberpunk 2077, and establish a full set of gameplay mechanics for that. Some things I'm wondering about now are,}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\widctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af10\langfe2052\ql\ltrpar\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\widctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af10\langfe2052\ql\ltrpar{\loch
1.) Would there be any sort of conflict between the two, and}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\widctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af10\langfe2052\ql\ltrpar{\loch
2.) Would this result in some grossly overpowered builds that would end up simply making the game too easy?}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\widctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af10\langfe2052\ql\ltrpar\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\widctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af10\langfe2052\ql\ltrpar\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\widctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af10\langfe2052\ql\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa283\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
1. Conflict Between Minmax Questlines/Interactions and the Overclock System?Minimal to none, if designed with intent. Here's why it works well together:}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af6 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\f6\dbch\af6 \u57352\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls7 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Your Minmax-Builds folders (the 35+ stat combinations + unique high/low interactions, questlines, secret endings) are primarily narrative and reactivity tools. They reward extreme stat spreads with special story content, companion reactions (e.g. Calethina), faction shifts, and unique paths.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af6 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\f6\dbch\af6 \u57352\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls7 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
The Overclock system is a gameplay/combat tool (cyberware ability with modes). It doesn't have to override or conflict with that reactivity\u8212\'97it can enhance it.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\ql\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Synergies you can build in:}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af6 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\f6\dbch\af6 \u57352\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls8 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Different MACHINE stat extremes naturally map to different Overclock strengths (high Agility/Engine \u8594\'3f better Framejacking; high Might \u8594\'3f stronger Berserk; high Calculation \u8594\'3f better Overclock spam).}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af6 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\f6\dbch\af6 \u57352\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls8 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
You can add unique interactions inside the existing Minmax-Builds subfolders: e.g., "High Engine + low Nerve" builds get a stronger but riskier version with special quest triggers or secret ending variants tied to "overclock addiction" or cyberpsychosis events.}
