2. Risk of Grossly Overpowered Builds Making the Game Too Easy?Yes \u8212\'97 this is the bigger concern, especially in a deep AP-driven turn-based system like yours.In turn-based grid games, "extra actions," massive damage buffs, or reduced costs are some of the strongest things you can add. A poorly balanced Sandevistan/Framejacking equivalent could let optimized high-Agility/Engine minmax builds delete encounters or trivialize exploration. Berserk mode on a high-Might build could turn bosses into jokes. Overclock spam on Calculation builds could break ability economy.However, this risk aligns perfectly with your design goals:}
